node.text:
The only regret I had during the last recession is that I didn't double down. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Looking back at the time now, I feel as if I could have done more with my business and more with real estate.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
As someone who's lived through a recession, my advice to you is don't hold back.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
You still need to be careful, because this isn't a housing crash but instead is more health related. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Being at home isn't an excuse to stop your business, keep pushing forward.

node.text:
Hoard Cash or Reinvest⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I've been asked this question numerous times since the lockdown, and I've had the same basic answer for most people.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
✅ Get your marketing straight. When the lockdown is over and people go back to living their normal lives your business will be stronger because you invested in your business.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
✅  Invest in your self. This advice is probably one of the most important pieces you'll have this lockdown. Working on your self during normal times is a good idea, working on yourself during a crisis is an even better idea.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
✅ Don't panic, tough times never last.⁠⠀

node.text:
💳 🚨⁠
⁠
We've talked about how it takes money to make money. Although you can make money without having any money, the difficulty is higher. ⁠
⁠
Good Credit allows you to create the liquidity you need to invest in things that will make you more money.⁠
⁠
Lenders use credit score to determine how much money they can trust you with. Having better credit opens up the doors to new opportunities.⁠
⁠
Be smart 🧠 and use your credit to make you more money.⁠
⁠
🚨 DM me about credit repair 🚨

node.text:
If you’re looking to hire an employee, you MUST look for these qualities. These qualities will guide you in finding an employee that will not only help you grow your business but truly care for your vision with the same spark that you do.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Team Player⁠⠀
This is a quality that you should not look over. If you find the right team player employee not only do they get their job done but they raise the morale and productivity of others around them.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Savvy⁠⠀
People must know how to do their job, or at least be knowledgeable and willing to learn. When looking for a new employee, hiring a highly skilled person reduces the load the entire team feels. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Open⁠⠀
An employee must be open to learn, and grow. They won’t always have all the answers or always be right. An important quality for them to compensate is for them to be open. If they are open to being wrong and learning a new way to do something they bring more value to the team as a whole.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Adaptable⁠⠀
Industries change rapidly. The demands of certain roles change as rapidly as the industry does, and in saying that employees must be able to get with the times and adapt. ⁠⠀

node.title: What Do I Look For When Hiring?

node.text:
Time heals all wounds. Throughout your life you learn to believe this saying more and more. Learning this helps you be more courageous with the risks you take. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
From my experience, things tend to work themselves out on their own anyway. Try not to stress about small things. That doesn’t mean that you don’t work to get problems solved, but it does mean that you don't let problems affect you for extended periods of time. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
What helps me relax is going home and being with my family. When with your family you know you’re supported and in your comfort zone. Being in your comfort zone for a long period of time is not good, but is a blessing at the end of a tough day.

node.text:
Best advice I ever got was from my mom.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Your mom is going to be one of the most critical guides in your life. When I was younger I was rebellious and didn’t pay much attention to the advice she was giving me. Once I grew older I realized the wisdom that she was trying to teach me and that I was pushing away.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
One of the most important things she ever said to me was “pior donde venimos, no vamos,” which roughly translates to “worse where we came, we won’t go.” This gave me the courage to move forward with the business ventures that I was unsure about.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Sure enough, when I took the advice and kept moving forward everything fell into place. With hard work and great people on my team.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
My question to you is:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
What is the worst thing that can happen?

node.text:
As you progress in life you begin to value loyalty more and more. You learn that people don’t always have your best interest at heart.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I grew up in a neighborhood where we were a family. Meaning we all played together, we all laughed together, and we all defended each other together. This is a dynamic that I carry with me to this day. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I look at the people in my team with the same compassion as I had for the other children in my neighborhood growing up.⁠⠀
⁠⠀

node.text:
Once an entrepreneur, always an entrepreneur. When I was younger I basically created a paper delivery franchise. Where as a teen I would reach over 900 hundred homes.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
This all started when I began working with a newspaper company where I would wake up early in morning and begin to prepare papers and my route for the day. Eventually I began to hire my friends to help me reach more homes. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
At a young age I learned how to scale a business and the importance of implementing systems to sustain growth. I ultimately left the paper route business, but the lessons learned during the process were priceless.

node.text:
“Throw it in the gutter, and go buy another.” When you begin to realize that a big part of maturing in business is being able to overcome failures. Failing is going to happen regardless whether it’s in your business life, personal life, or any other aspect of your life.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I’ve encountered people who are attached to their business for years and years yet they aren't successful. They never go anywhere or try anything new because they are stuck in their old ways. There is a difference between perseverance and being wrong.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
When you realize that you’ve done everything that you can to make your business be successful and perseverance is not helping then it’s time to “throw it in the gutter.” After doing that you need to “buy another,” whether that’s a new business, idea, or product you need to get out of your comfort zone. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Keep pushing forward.  #investing #realestateinvesting #investingtips #bitcoininvesting #investingforbeginners #investing101 #investors #money #moneymaker #business #investorshub #businessowner #onlinebusinesscoach #work #network #businessadvice #businessinsider

node.text:
Imagine being at home, relaxing with your family, and answering the door to a new #perspective .

Once at the door, I realized he wasn’t just any salesman.

After talking to him I realized he was different. The conversation then shifted to #business , #money , and #sales. 
He was making $250k a year working 5 days a week selling vacuums.

This goes to show that without any experience and a bit of #practice and #determination you could change your life.
